I"Å<p>The Grunt ecosystem is huge and it‚Äôs growing every day. With literally hundreds of plugins to choose from, you can use Grunt to automate just about anything with a minimum of effort. If someone hasn‚Äôt already built what you need, authoring and publishing your own Grunt plugin to npm is a breeze. See how to <a href="http://gruntjs.com/">get started</a>.</p>

<p>In one word: automation. The less work you have to do when performing repetitive tasks like minification, compilation, unit testing, linting, etc, the easier your job becomes. After you‚Äôve configured it through a Gruntfile, a task runner can do most of that mundane work for you‚Äîand your team‚Äîwith basically zero effort.</p>

<p>Jekyll also offers powerful support for code snippets:</p>

